text: "Supersonic" is a 1999 song by English funk band Jamiroquai and is the third single from their fourth studio album Synkronized. It went to number 22 in the United Kingdom and Scotland, number 75 in the Netherlands and number 3 in Iceland. It topped the Billboard Dance Club Songs charts. ==Track listings== * UK CD1 # "Supersonic" (radio edit) – 3:41 # "Supersonic" (Pete Heller – The Love mix) – 9:35 # "Supersonic" (Harvey's Fuel Altered mix) – 6:35 * UK CD2 # "Supersonic" – 5:15 # "Supersonic" (Restless Soul main vocal) – 7:35 # "Supersonic" (Sharp Razor remix) – 7:04 * UK cassette single # "Supersonic" (radio edit) – 3:41 # "Supersonic" – 5:15 ==References== Category:1999 songs Category:Jamiroquai songs
